<TITLE> Ctg journos stop work to seek new pay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com)  Journalists and employees of seven newspapers in Chittagong observed a one-hour work stoppage for a second day on Thursday in support of their demand of pay in line with the seventh wage board. Called by the Chittagong Journalists Union, working journalists refrained from work from 7pm. The suspension of work was observed at the offices of Dainik Azadi, Dainik Purbokon, Dainik Suprobhat Bangladesh, Dainik Bir Chottogram Moncho, Dainik Noya Bangla, Dainik Karnaphuli and Daily People's View. "We have observed a token suspension of work demanding the implementation of the seventh wage board," said Nazimuddin Shaymol, general secretary of Chittagong Union of Journalists. "If the newspaper owners do not comply, then strict programmes will be declared next month." A mass campaign of journalists will be carried out on Dec. 15 for going into a full scale strike, he added. "We will also have meetings with the paper owners," Shyamol said. b
